> This dish takes its name from the Korean word for mixing rice. Which is exactly what you're meant to do after serving it: Put your rice in a bowl, add the toppings, and mix it all together so that those flavors and textures combine in a glorious mishmash. There are plenty of flavors and textures going on here, too, like sweet carrot, tender zucchini, and pork tossed with garlic, ginger, and soy sauce.

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and peel @Carrots{6%oz}. Using a #peeler{}, shave carrots lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core; discard core. Trim and halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Peel and mince @Ginger{1%thumb} and @Garlic{1%clove}.

== Pickled Scallions ==

In a small #bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @White Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sesame Oil{1%tbsp}, @Gochujang Sauce{1/2%oz}, half the @Soy Sauce{2%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), and @Sugar{1%tbsp}. Stir until sugar has dissolved.

== Carrots and Zucchini ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tbsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add another drizzle of oil to pan. Add zucchini; season with salt and pepper. Cook until browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside with carrots.

== Pork ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Pork{10%oz}, ginger, and garlic. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until pork is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add remaining soy sauce and cook, stirring, until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper; divide between bowls.

Arrange pork and veggies over rice. Top with pickled scallion whites (and pickling liquid). Drizzle with sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.